@Arun Ramprasadh today ott merchants generally pass the mandate max amount of as the order amount itself, this is mainly because in UPI mandates though the user is shown the order amount and the mandate max amount on the summary screen of the PSP app, on the NPCI pin screen the user sees the Mandate max amount as the amount. This causes a lot of drop offs, for example, when tatabinge had gone live they had plans ranging from 199 to 699 but we setting the mandate max amount as 3000 so that they can account for any price variations at a later stage and do not have to set up new mandates to retain customers. But since the user was seeing amount as 3000 on the Pin screen they had seen a lot of drop offs when they went live. Post which they have moved to passing the order amount as the mandate max amount. Due to this have they had to reach out to customers whenever there is a price change to collect the difference and set up new mandates.
We recently saw alerts <https://juspay.slack.com/archives/C031C64PH32/p1714921572776909|here> for another ott merchant where they had updated their pricing and now has to reach out to customers to set up new mandates. Can we reach out to NPCI to show both the mandate max amount and the order amount on the PIN screen this would give confidence to the users that the debit is happening only for the order amount and not the mandate max amount.
